NIGHT.

In
the
hotel
garden,
some
cats
were
singing.
A
dog

them
with

much
barking
;
then
came
back

out

tongue,
blue
from

or

pens.
While
we

trunks,
in

disor

der,

Isabelle

in
the
hall.
She
was
a
little
woman,

excessively
preserved
by
milk
of
cucumbers
and
egotism
;
her
wrinkles
knotted

behind
her
ears,
her
bosom
sowed
with
a
row
of
false
pearls
whose
nautical

originals
she
held
in
her
hand
in
a
little
bag
of
crocodile
skin.

When
she
saw
me
she
cried
out:

"
I

my
daughter
to
you.
Isabelle
does
not
want
to
go
back
to
France

with
me.
She
permits
no
constraint.
She
is
like
the
air.
Nothing
matters
to

her.
You,
Monsieur,
you
are
a
scholar,
a
man
of
sense
;
watch

her.
Where

is
she
?
She
is
here
no
longer.
Gone
God

where,
without
a
maid.
She

has
carried
off
some
bottles,
a
quilt,
and
a
spade
with

to
kill
lizards,
saying

that
she
hoped
for
nothing
more
from
me
and
that
my
hypocrisy
irritated
her.

This
young
lady
drinks
like
a
sink,
and
all
liquors
without
distinction.
Nothing

which
used
to
amuse
us,
the
four
step,
Hungarian
lace,
the

show,

her.
Every

years
the
world
sheds
a
skin
and
us

At
your
age,

tell
her,
I

children.

replies

belly.
'

indifferent
to
clothes
;

out

My

and
my
prejudices
enchant
her.
She
en

She

nothing.

No
taste
for
art.
That
which

writes
has
no
sense.
Morally
one
would
say

that
she
has
gone
to
pieces
;
she
is

prey
;

congratulates
herself

that

at

accursed
but
laughs

about

I
shall

fruit.

?
